begin
reserve V for RealLinearSpace;
theorem
Th28: (for v being (VECTOR of V) holds (for X being (Subspace of V) holds (for y being (VECTOR of ( X + ( Lin { v } ) )) holds (for W being (Subspace of ( X + ( Lin { v } ) )) holds (((v = y & X = W) & (not v in X)) implies (for w being (VECTOR of ( X + ( Lin { v } ) )) holds (ex x being (VECTOR of X) st (ex r being Real st ( w |-- (W,( Lin { y } )) ) = [ x,( r * v ) ]))))))))
proof
let v being (VECTOR of V);
let X being (Subspace of V);
let y being (VECTOR of ( X + ( Lin { v } ) ));
let W being (Subspace of ( X + ( Lin { v } ) ));
assume that
A1: v = y
and
A2: X = W
and
A3: (not v in X);
let w being (VECTOR of ( X + ( Lin { v } ) ));
consider v1,v2 being (VECTOR of ( X + ( Lin { v } ) )) such that A4: ( w |-- (W,( Lin { y } )) ) = [ v1,v2 ] by CKB14:1;
A5: ( X + ( Lin { v } ) ) is_the_direct_sum_of W,( Lin { y } ) by A1,A2,A3,CKB11:1;
then v1 in W by A4,CKB4:1;
then reconsider x = v1 as (VECTOR of X) by A2,STRUCT_0:def 5;
v2 in ( Lin { y } ) by A5,A4,CKB4:1;
then consider r being Real such that A6: v2 = ( r * y ) by RLVECT_4:8;
take x;
take r;
thus thesis by A1,A4,A6,RLSUB_1:14;
end;
